article_title: Open enrollment starts for Obamacare’s second year
article_text: Open enrollment began Saturday for the second year of health insurance reforms under the federal Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act. The state’s health exchange, Covered California, is reaching out to African Americans, Latinos and Asian Americans in an effort to sign up 1.7 million more users.
